The paper deals with the analysis of Boolean functions, which is a central topic in theoretical computer science. The use of Fourier analysis and total influence is common in the study of Boolean functions, which suggests that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses learning algorithms for sparse functions, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper touches on the topic of Fourier entropy, which is related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
